During a press briefing, White House Press Secretary Sarah Sanders addressed several topics including the recent heroic landing of Southwest Flight 1380, a suicide bombing in Kabul, questions from the Office of the Special Counsel, Chief of Staff John Kelly's position, the Iran nuclear deal, and the ongoing negotiations on steel and aluminum tariffs. Sanders also addressed questions about the President's personal attorney, Michael Cohen, and the President's response to the defamation lawsuit filed by Stormy Daniels. Other topics discussed include the President's meeting with Kim Jong-un, the California lawsuit over EPA fuel standards, and the President's upcoming speech at the NRA convention. Sanders also mentioned that the President will be meeting with potential candidates for the Secretary of Veterans Affairs position and that there is no change to the current Afghanistan policy.